  22"""Concrete implementations of the library's deserialization framework.
  23
  24Exports
  25-------
  26* `Framework`: The default deserialization framework that's used within client impl's.
  27* `Empty`: An empty deserialization framework, it can be used standalone without the need of a client owner.
  28"""
  29
  30from __future__ import annotations
  31
  32__all__ = ("Framework", "Empty")

  35

  67class Framework(api.Framework):
  68    """The base deserialization framework implementation.
  69
  70    This framework is used to deserialize JSON responses from the REST client and turning them into a `aiobungie.crates` Python classes.
  71
  72    Example
  73    --------
  74    ```py
  75    import aiobungie
  76
  77    from aiobungie import traits
  78    from aiobungie import framework
  79    from aiobungie import crates
  80
  81    class MyClient(traits.Deserialize):
  82        rest = aiobungie.RESTClient("token")
  83        my_name = "Fate"
  84        my_code = 4275
  85
  86        @property # required method.
  87        def framework(self) -> framework.Empty:
  88            return framework.Empty()
  89
  90        async def my_memberships(self) -> tuple[crates.DestinyMembership, ...]:
  91            # Note, Do not call methods within objects, Since this is an empty
  92            # factory, The client reference that makes these calls will be `None`.
  93            response = await self.rest.fetch_membership(self.my_name, self.my_code)
  94            return self.factory.deserialize_destiny_memberships(response)
  95
  96    async def main() -> None:
  97        client = MyClient()
  98        async with client.rest:
  99            print(await client.my_memberships())
 100
 101    asyncio.run(main())
 102    ```
 103    """
 104
 105    __slots__ = ("_app",)

 107    def __init__(self) -> None:

 110    def deserialize_bungie_user(self, data: typedefs.JSONObject) -> user.BungieUser:
 111        return user.BungieUser(
 112            id=int(data["membershipId"]),
 113            created_at=time.clean_date(data["firstAccess"]),
 114            name=data.get("cachedBungieGlobalDisplayName"),
 115            is_deleted=data["isDeleted"],
 116            about=data["about"],
 117            updated_at=time.clean_date(data["lastUpdate"]),
 118            psn_name=data.get("psnDisplayName", None),
 119            stadia_name=data.get("stadiaDisplayName", None),
 120            steam_name=data.get("steamDisplayName", None),
 121            twitch_name=data.get("twitchDisplayName", None),
 122            blizzard_name=data.get("blizzardDisplayName", None),
 123            egs_name=data.get("egsDisplayName", None),
 124            status=data["statusText"],
 125            locale=data["locale"],
 126            picture=builders.Image(path=data["profilePicturePath"]),
 127            code=data.get("cachedBungieGlobalDisplayNameCode", None),
 128            unique_name=data.get("uniqueName", None),
 129            theme_id=int(data["profileTheme"]),
 130            show_activity=bool(data["showActivity"]),
 131            theme_name=data["profileThemeName"],
 132            display_title=data["userTitleDisplay"],
 133            profile_ban_expire=time.clean_date(data["profileBanExpire"])
 134            if "profileBanExpire" in data
 135            else None,
 136        )
 137
 138    def deserialize_partial_bungie_user(
 139        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 140    ) -> user.PartialBungieUser:
 141        return user.PartialBungieUser(
 142            types=tuple(
 143                enums.MembershipType(type_)
 144                for type_ in payload.get("applicableMembershipTypes", ())
 145            ),
 146            name=payload["bungieGlobalDisplayName"]
 147            if "bungieGlobalDisplayName" in payload
 148            else payload.get("displayName"),
 149            id=int(payload["membershipId"]),
 150            crossave_override=enums.MembershipType(payload["crossSaveOverride"]),
 151            is_public=payload["isPublic"],
 152            icon=builders.Image(path=payload.get("iconPath", "")),
 153            type=enums.MembershipType(payload["membershipType"]),
 154            code=payload.get("bungieGlobalDisplayNameCode"),
 155        )
 156
 157    def deserialize_destiny_membership(
 158        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 159    ) -> user.DestinyMembership:
 160        name: str | None = None
 161        if (raw_name := payload.get("bungieGlobalDisplayName")) is not None:
 162            name = typedefs.unknown(raw_name)
 163
 164        return user.DestinyMembership(
 165            id=int(payload["membershipId"]),
 166            name=name,
 167            code=payload.get("bungieGlobalDisplayNameCode", None),
 168            last_seen_name=payload.get("LastSeenDisplayName")
 169            or payload.get("displayName")  # noqa: W503
 170            or "",  # noqa: W503
 171            type=enums.MembershipType(payload["membershipType"]),
 172            is_public=payload["isPublic"],
 173            crossave_override=enums.MembershipType(payload["crossSaveOverride"]),
 174            icon=builders.Image(path=payload.get("iconPath", "")),
 175            types=tuple(
 176                enums.MembershipType(type_)
 177                for type_ in payload.get("applicableMembershipTypes", ())
 178            ),
 179        )
 180
 181    def deserialize_destiny_memberships(
 182        self, data: typedefs.JSONArray
 183    ) -> collections.Sequence[user.DestinyMembership]:
 184        return tuple(
 185            self.deserialize_destiny_membership(membership) for membership in data
 186        )
 187
 188    def deserialize_user(self, data: typedefs.JSONObject) -> user.User:
 189        primary_membership_id: int | None = None
 190        if raw_primary_id := data.get("primaryMembershipId"):
 191            primary_membership_id = int(raw_primary_id)
 192
 193        return user.User(
 194            bungie_user=self.deserialize_bungie_user(data["bungieNetUser"]),
 195            memberships=self.deserialize_destiny_memberships(
 196                data["destinyMemberships"]
 197            ),
 198            primary_membership_id=primary_membership_id,
 199        )
 200
 201    def deserialize_sanitized_membership(
 202        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 203    ) -> user.SanitizedMembership:
 204        return user.SanitizedMembership(
 205            epic_games=payload.get("EgsId"),
 206            psn=payload.get("PsnId"),
 207            steam=payload.get("SteamId"),
 208            xbox=payload.get("XboxId"),
 209            twitch=payload.get("TwitchId"),
 210        )
 211
 212    def deserialize_searched_user(
 213        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 214    ) -> user.SearchableDestinyUser:
 215        code: int | None = None
 216        if raw_code := payload.get("bungieGlobalDisplayNameCode"):
 217            code = int(raw_code)
 218
 219        bungie_id: int | None = None
 220        if raw_bungie_id := payload.get("bungieNetMembershipId"):
 221            bungie_id = int(raw_bungie_id)
 222
 223        return user.SearchableDestinyUser(
 224            name=typedefs.unknown(payload["bungieGlobalDisplayName"]),
 225            code=code,
 226            bungie_id=bungie_id,
 227            memberships=self.deserialize_destiny_memberships(
 228                payload["destinyMemberships"]
 229            ),
 230        )
 231
 232    def deserialize_user_credentials(
 233        self, payload: typedefs.JSONArray
 234    ) -> collections.Sequence[user.UserCredentials]:
 235        return tuple(
 236            user.UserCredentials(
 237                type=enums.CredentialType(int(credit["credentialType"])),
 238                display_name=credit["credentialDisplayName"],
 239                is_public=credit["isPublic"],
 240                self_as_string=credit.get("credentialAsString"),
 241            )
 242            for credit in payload
 243        )

 245    def deserialize_user_themes(
 246        self, payload: typedefs.JSONArray
 247    ) -> collections.Sequence[user.UserThemes]:
 248        return tuple(
 249            user.UserThemes(
 250                id=int(entry["userThemeId"]),
 251                name=entry["userThemeName"] if "userThemeName" in entry else None,
 252                description=entry["userThemeDescription"]
 253                if "userThemeDescription" in entry
 254                else None,
 255            )
 256            for entry in payload
 257        )

 259    def deserialize_group(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> clans.Group:
 260        clan_info_obj: typedefs.JSONObject | None = None
 261        if raw_clan_info := payload.get("clanInfo"):
 262            clan_info_obj = clans.ClanInfo(
 263                call_sign=raw_clan_info["clanCallsign"],
 264                banner_data=raw_clan_info["clanBannerData"],
 265            )
 266        return clans.Group(
 267            group_id=int(payload["groupId"]),
 268            name=payload["name"],
 269            creation_date=time.clean_date(payload["creationDate"]),
 270            about=payload["about"],
 271            clan_info=clan_info_obj,
 272            motto=payload.get("motto"),
 273            member_count=int(payload["memberCount"]),
 274            locale=payload["locale"],
 275            membership_option=int(payload["membershipOption"]),
 276            capabilities=int(payload["capabilities"]),
 277            remote_group_id=int(payload["remoteGroupId"])
 278            if "remoteGroupId" in payload
 279            else None,
 280            group_type=enums.GroupType(int(payload["groupType"])),
 281            avatar_path=builders.Image(payload["avatarPath"]),
 282            theme=payload["theme"],
 283        )
 284
 285    def _deserialize_group_details(
 286        self,
 287        data: typedefs.JSONObject,
 288        current_user_memberships: collections.Mapping[str, clans.ClanMember]
 289        | None = None,
 290        clan_founder: clans.ClanMember | None = None,
 291    ) -> clans.Clan:
 292        features = data["features"]
 293        features_obj = clans.ClanFeatures(
 294            max_members=features["maximumMembers"],
 295            max_membership_types=features["maximumMembershipsOfGroupType"],
 296            capabilities=features["capabilities"],
 297            membership_types=features["membershipTypes"],
 298            invite_permissions=features["invitePermissionOverride"],
 299            update_banner_permissions=features["updateBannerPermissionOverride"],
 300            update_culture_permissions=features["updateCulturePermissionOverride"],
 301            join_level=features["joinLevel"],
 302        )
 303        information: typedefs.JSONObject = data["clanInfo"]
 304        progression: collections.Mapping[int, progressions.Progression] = {
 305            int(prog_hash): self.deserialize_progressions(prog)
 306            for prog_hash, prog in information["d2ClanProgressions"].items()
 307        }
 308
 309        return clans.Clan(
 310            id=int(data["groupId"]),
 311            name=data["name"],
 312            type=enums.GroupType(data["groupType"]),
 313            created_at=time.clean_date(data["creationDate"]),
 314            member_count=data["memberCount"],
 315            motto=data["motto"],
 316            about=data["about"],
 317            is_public=data["isPublic"],
 318            banner=builders.Image(path=data["bannerPath"]),
 319            avatar=builders.Image(path=data["avatarPath"]),
 320            tags=tuple(data["tags"]),
 321            features=features_obj,
 322            owner=clan_founder,
 323            progressions=progression,
 324            call_sign=information["clanCallsign"],
 325            banner_data=information["clanBannerData"],
 326            chat_security=data["chatSecurity"],
 327            conversation_id=int(data["conversationId"]),
 328            allow_chat=data["allowChat"],
 329            theme=data["theme"],
 330            current_user_membership=current_user_memberships,
 331        )
 332
 333    def deserialize_clan(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> clans.Clan:
 334        current_user_map: collections.Mapping[str, clans.ClanMember] | None = None
 335        if raw_current_user := payload.get("currentUserMemberMap"):
 336            # This will get populated if only it was a GroupsV2.GroupResponse.
 337            # GroupsV2.GetGroupsForMemberResponse doesn't have this field.
 338            current_user_map = {
 339                membership_type: self.deserialize_clan_member(membership)
 340                for membership_type, membership in raw_current_user.items()
 341            }
 342
 343        return self._deserialize_group_details(
 344            data=payload["detail"],
 345            clan_founder=self.deserialize_clan_member(payload["founder"]),
 346            current_user_memberships=current_user_map,
 347        )
 348
 349    def deserialize_clan_member(self, data: typedefs.JSONObject, /) -> clans.ClanMember:
 350        destiny_user = self.deserialize_destiny_membership(data["destinyUserInfo"])
 351        return clans.ClanMember(
 352            last_seen_name=destiny_user.last_seen_name,
 353            id=destiny_user.id,
 354            name=destiny_user.name,
 355            icon=destiny_user.icon,
 356            last_online=time.from_timestamp(int(data["lastOnlineStatusChange"])),
 357            group_id=int(data["groupId"]),
 358            joined_at=time.clean_date(data["joinDate"]),
 359            types=destiny_user.types,
 360            is_public=destiny_user.is_public,
 361            type=destiny_user.type,
 362            code=destiny_user.code,
 363            is_online=data["isOnline"],
 364            crossave_override=destiny_user.crossave_override,
 365            bungie_user=self.deserialize_partial_bungie_user(data["bungieNetUserInfo"])
 366            if "bungieNetUserInfo" in data
 367            else None,
 368            member_type=enums.ClanMemberType(int(data["memberType"])),
 369        )
 370
 371    def deserialize_clan_members(
 372        self, data: typedefs.JSONObject, /
 373    ) -> sain.Iterator[clans.ClanMember]:
 374        return sain.Iter(
 375            self.deserialize_clan_member(member) for member in data["results"]
 376        )
 377
 378    def deserialize_group_member(
 379        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 380    ) -> clans.GroupMember:
 381        member = payload["member"]
 382        return clans.GroupMember(
 383            join_date=time.clean_date(member["joinDate"]),
 384            group_id=int(member["groupId"]),
 385            member_type=enums.ClanMemberType(member["memberType"]),
 386            is_online=member["isOnline"],
 387            last_online=time.from_timestamp(int(member["lastOnlineStatusChange"])),
 388            inactive_memberships=payload.get("areAllMembershipsInactive", None),
 389            member=self.deserialize_destiny_membership(member["destinyUserInfo"]),
 390            group=self._deserialize_group_details(payload["group"]),
 391        )

 393    def _deserialize_clan_conversation(
 394        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 395    ) -> clans.ClanConversation:
 396        return clans.ClanConversation(
 397            id=int(payload["conversationId"]),
 398            group_id=int(payload["groupId"]),
 399            name=typedefs.unknown(payload["chatName"]),
 400            chat_enabled=payload["chatEnabled"],
 401            security=payload["chatSecurity"],
 402        )

 438    def _set_character_attrs(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> character.Character:
 439        if raw_emblem_color := payload.get("emblemColor"):
 440            emblem_color: tuple[int, int, int, int] = (
 441                int(raw_emblem_color["red"]),
 442                int(raw_emblem_color["green"]),
 443                int(raw_emblem_color["blue"]),
 444                int(raw_emblem_color["alpha"]),
 445            )
 446        else:
 447            emblem_color = (0, 0, 0, 0)
 448
 449        return character.Character(
 450            id=int(payload["characterId"]),
 451            gender=enums.Gender(payload["genderType"]),
 452            race=enums.Race(payload["raceType"]),
 453            class_type=enums.Class(payload["classType"]),
 454            emblem=builders.Image(path=payload["emblemBackgroundPath"])
 455            if "emblemBackgroundPath" in payload
 456            else None,
 457            emblem_icon=builders.Image(path=payload["emblemPath"])
 458            if "emblemPath" in payload
 459            else None,
 460            emblem_hash=int(payload["emblemHash"]) if "emblemHash" in payload else None,
 461            last_played=time.clean_date(payload["dateLastPlayed"]),
 462            total_played_time=int(payload["minutesPlayedTotal"]),
 463            member_id=int(payload["membershipId"]),
 464            member_type=enums.MembershipType(payload["membershipType"]),
 465            level=payload["baseCharacterLevel"],
 466            title_hash=payload.get("titleRecordHash", None),
 467            light=payload["light"],
 468            stats={enums.Stat(int(k)): v for k, v in payload["stats"].items()},
 469            emblem_color=emblem_color,
 470            minutes_played_this_session=int(payload["minutesPlayedThisSession"])
 471            if "minutesPlayedThisSession" in payload
 472            else 0,
 473            percent_to_next_level=float(payload["percentToNextLevel"]),
 474        )

 476    def deserialize_profile(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject, /) -> profile.Profile:
 477        return profile.Profile(
 478            user=self.deserialize_destiny_membership(payload["userInfo"]),
 479            last_played=time.clean_date(payload["dateLastPlayed"]),
 480            versions_owned=enums.GameVersions(int(payload["versionsOwned"])),
 481            character_ids=tuple(
 482                int(character_id) for character_id in payload["characterIds"]
 483            ),
 484            season_hashes=tuple(payload["seasonHashes"]),
 485            event_card_hashes=tuple(payload["eventCardHashesOwned"]),
 486            season_hash=payload["currentSeasonHash"],
 487            power_cap=payload["currentSeasonRewardPowerCap"],
 488            guardian_rank=payload["currentGuardianRank"],
 489            highest_guardian_rank=payload["lifetimeHighestGuardianRank"],
 490            renewed_guardian_rank=payload["renewedGuardianRank"],
 491        )

 493    def deserialize_profile_item(
 494        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 495    ) -> profile.ProfileItemImpl:
 496        instance_id: int | None = None
 497        if raw_instance_id := payload.get("itemInstanceId"):
 498            instance_id = int(raw_instance_id)
 499
 500        version_number: int | None = None
 501        if raw_version := payload.get("versionNumber"):
 502            version_number = int(raw_version)
 503
 504        transfer_status = enums.TransferStatus(payload["transferStatus"])
 505
 506        return profile.ProfileItemImpl(
 507            hash=payload["itemHash"],
 508            quantity=payload["quantity"],
 509            bind_status=enums.ItemBindStatus(payload["bindStatus"]),
 510            location=enums.ItemLocation(payload["location"]),
 511            bucket=payload["bucketHash"],
 512            transfer_status=transfer_status,
 513            lockable=payload["lockable"],
 514            state=enums.ItemState(payload["state"]),
 515            dismantle_permissions=payload["dismantlePermission"],
 516            is_wrapper=payload["isWrapper"],
 517            instance_id=instance_id,
 518            version_number=version_number,
 519            ornament_id=payload.get("overrideStyleItemHash"),
 520        )

 522    def deserialize_objectives(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> records.Objective:
 523        return records.Objective(
 524            hash=payload["objectiveHash"],
 525            visible=payload["visible"],
 526            complete=payload["complete"],
 527            completion_value=payload["completionValue"],
 528            progress=payload.get("progress"),
 529            destination_hash=payload.get("destinationHash"),
 530            activity_hash=payload.get("activityHash"),
 531        )

 536        payload: typedefs.JSONObject,
 537        scores: records.RecordScores | None = None,
 538        **nodes: int,
 539    ) -> records.Record:
 540        objectives: collections.Sequence[records.Objective] | None = None
 541        interval_objectives: collections.Sequence[records.Objective] | None = None
 542        record_state: records.RecordState | int
 543
 544        record_state = records.RecordState(payload["state"])
 545
 546        if raw_objs := payload.get("objectives"):
 547            objectives = tuple(self.deserialize_objectives(obj) for obj in raw_objs)
 548
 549        if raw_interval_objs := payload.get("intervalObjectives"):
 550            interval_objectives = tuple(
 551                self.deserialize_objectives(obj) for obj in raw_interval_objs
 552            )
 553
 554        return records.Record(
 555            scores=scores,
 556            categories_node_hash=nodes.get("categories_hash"),
 557            seals_node_hash=nodes.get("seals_hash"),
 558            state=record_state,
 559            objectives=objectives,
 560            interval_objectives=interval_objectives,
 561            redeemed_count=payload.get("intervalsRedeemedCount", 0),
 562            completion_times=payload.get("completedCount", None),
 563            reward_visibility=payload.get("rewardVisibility"),
 564        )

 831    def deserialize_milestone(
 832        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 833    ) -> milestones.Milestone:
 834        start_date: datetime.datetime | None = None
 835        if raw_start_date := payload.get("startDate"):
 836            start_date = time.clean_date(raw_start_date)
 837
 838        end_date: datetime.datetime | None = None
 839        if raw_end_date := payload.get("endDate"):
 840            end_date = time.clean_date(raw_end_date)
 841
 842        rewards: collections.Collection[milestones.MilestoneReward] | None = None
 843        if raw_rewards := payload.get("rewards"):
 844            rewards = tuple(
 845                self._deserialize_milestone_rewards(reward) for reward in raw_rewards
 846            )
 847
 848        activities: collections.Sequence[milestones.MilestoneActivity] | None = None
 849        if raw_activities := payload.get("activities"):
 850            activities = tuple(
 851                self._deserialize_milestone_activity(active)
 852                for active in raw_activities
 853            )
 854
 855        quests: collections.Sequence[milestones.MilestoneQuest] | None = None
 856        if raw_quests := payload.get("availableQuests"):
 857            quests = tuple(
 858                self._deserialize_milestone_available_quest(quest)
 859                for quest in raw_quests
 860            )
 861
 862        vendors: collections.Sequence[milestones.MilestoneVendor] | None = None
 863        if raw_vendors := payload.get("vendors"):
 864            vendors = tuple(
 865                milestones.MilestoneVendor(
 866                    vendor_hash=vendor["vendorHash"],
 867                    preview_itemhash=vendor.get("previewItemHash"),
 868                )
 869                for vendor in raw_vendors
 870            )
 871
 872        return milestones.Milestone(
 873            hash=payload["milestoneHash"],
 874            start_date=start_date,
 875            end_date=end_date,
 876            order=payload["order"],
 877            rewards=rewards,
 878            available_quests=quests,
 879            activities=activities,
 880            vendors=vendors,
 881        )

1113    def deserialize_components(  # noqa: C901 Too complex.
1114        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
1115    ) -> components.Component:
1116        # Due to how complex this method is, We'll stick to
1117        # typing.Optional here.
1118
1119        profile_: profile.Profile | None = None
1120        if raw_profile := payload.get("profile"):
1121            profile_ = self.deserialize_profile(raw_profile["data"])
1122
1123        profile_progression: profile.ProfileProgression | None = None
1124        if raw_profile_progression := payload.get("profileProgression"):
1125            profile_progression = self.deserialize_profile_progression(
1126                raw_profile_progression
1127            )
1128
1129        profile_currencies: typing.Optional[
1130            collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]
1131        ] = None
1132        if raw_profile_currencies := payload.get("profileCurrencies"):
1133            if "data" in raw_profile_currencies:
1134                profile_currencies = self.deserialize_profile_items(
1135                    raw_profile_currencies["data"]
1136                )
1137
1138        profile_inventories: typing.Optional[
1139            collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]
1140        ] = None
1141        if raw_profile_inventories := payload.get("profileInventory"):
1142            if "data" in raw_profile_inventories:
1143                profile_inventories = self.deserialize_profile_items(
1144                    raw_profile_inventories["data"]
1145                )
1146
1147        profile_records: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, records.Record]] = (
1148            None
1149        )
1150
1151        if raw_profile_records_ := payload.get("profileRecords"):
1152            profile_records = self.deserialize_profile_records(raw_profile_records_)
1153
1154        characters: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, character.Character]] = (
1155            None
1156        )
1157        if raw_characters := payload.get("characters"):
1158            characters = self.deserialize_characters(raw_characters)
1159
1160        character_records: typing.Optional[
1161            collections.Mapping[int, records.CharacterRecord]
1162        ] = None
1163
1164        if raw_character_records := payload.get("characterRecords"):
1165            # Had to do it in two steps..
1166            to_update = {}
1167            for _, data in raw_character_records["data"].items():
1168                for record_id, record in data.items():
1169                    to_update[record_id] = record
1170
1171            character_records = {
1172                int(rec_id): self.deserialize_character_records(

1405    def deserialize_items_component(
1406        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
1407    ) -> components.ItemsComponent:
1408        # Due to how complex this method is, We'll stick to typing.Optional.
1409        instances: typing.Optional[
1410            collections.Sequence[collections.Mapping[int, items.ItemInstance]]
1411        ] = None
1412        if raw_instances := payload.get("instances"):
1413            instances = tuple(
1414                {int(ins_id): self.deserialize_instanced_item(item)}
1415                for ins_id, item in raw_instances["data"].items()
1416            )
1417
1418        render_data: typing.Optional[
1419            collections.Mapping[int, tuple[bool, dict[int, int]]]
1420        ] = None
1421        if raw_render_data := payload.get("renderData"):
1422            render_data = {
1423                int(ins_id): (data["useCustomDyes"], data["artRegions"])
1424                for ins_id, data in raw_render_data["data"].items()
1425            }
1426
1427        stats: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, items.ItemStatsView]] = None
1428        if raw_stats := payload.get("stats"):
1429            stats = {}
1430            for ins_id, stat in raw_stats["data"].items():
1431                for _, items_ in stat.items():
1432                    stats[int(ins_id)] = self.deserialize_item_stats_view(items_)
1433
1434        sockets: typing.Optional[
1435            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[items.ItemSocket]]
1436        ] = None
1437        if raw_sockets := payload.get("sockets"):
1438            sockets = {
1439                int(ins_id): tuple(
1440                    self.deserialize_item_socket(socket) for socket in item["sockets"]
1441                )
1442                for ins_id, item in raw_sockets["data"].items()
1443            }
1444
1445        objectives: typing.Optional[
1446            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[records.Objective]]
1447        ] = None
1448        if raw_objectives := payload.get("objectives"):
1449            objectives = {
1450                int(ins_id): tuple(
1451                    self.deserialize_objectives(objective)
1452                    for objective in data["objectives"]
1453                )
1454                for ins_id, data in raw_objectives["data"].items()
1455            }
1456
1457        perks: typing.Optional[
1458            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Collection[items.ItemPerk]]
1459        ] = None
1460        if raw_perks := payload.get("perks"):
1461            perks = {
1462                int(ins_id): tuple(
1463                    self.deserialize_item_perk(perk) for perk in item["perks"]
1464                )
1465                for ins_id, item in raw_perks["data"].items()
1466            }
1467
1468        plug_states: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[items.PlugItemState]] = None
1469        if raw_plug_states := payload.get("plugStates"):
1470            plug_states = tuple(
1471                self.deserialize_plug_item_state(plug)
1472                for _, plug in raw_plug_states["data"].items()
1473            )
1474
1475        reusable_plugs: typing.Optional[
1476            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[items.PlugItemState]]
1477        ] = None
1478        if raw_re_plugs := payload.get("reusablePlugs"):
1479            reusable_plugs = {
1480                int(ins_id): tuple(
1481                    self.deserialize_plug_item_state(state) for state in inner
1482                )
1483                for ins_id, plug in raw_re_plugs["data"].items()
1484                for inner in tuple(plug["plugs"].values())
1485            }
1486
1487        plug_objectives: typing.Optional[
1488            collections.Mapping[
1489                int, collections.Mapping[int, collections.Collection[records.Objective]]
1490            ]
1491        ] = None
1492        if raw_plug_objectives := payload.get("plugObjectives"):
1493            plug_objectives = {
1494                int(ins_id): {
1495                    int(obj_hash): tuple(
1496                        self.deserialize_objectives(obj) for obj in objs
1497                    )
1498                    for obj_hash, objs in inner["objectivesPerPlug"].items()
1499                }
1500                for ins_id, inner in raw_plug_objectives["data"].items()
1501            }
1502
1503        return components.ItemsComponent(
1504            sockets=sockets,
1505            stats=stats,
1506            render_data=render_data,
1507            instances=instances,
1508            objectives=objectives,
1509            perks=perks,
1510            plug_states=plug_states,
1511            reusable_plugs=reusable_plugs,
1512            plug_objectives=plug_objectives,
1513        )

1515    def deserialize_character_component(
1516        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
1517    ) -> components.CharacterComponent:
1518        character_: character.Character | None = None

1530                if "data" in raw_loadouts:
1531                    loadouts = tuple(
1532                        self.deserialize_character_loadout(loadout)
1533                        # very interesting nesting bungie...
1534                        for loadout in raw_loadouts["data"]["loadouts"]
1535                    )
1536
1537        activities: activity.CharacterActivity | None = None
1538        if raw_activities := payload.get("activities"):

1540
1541        equipment: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]] = None
1542        if raw_equipments := payload.get("equipment"):
1543            equipment = self.deserialize_profile_items(raw_equipments["data"])
1544
1545        progressions_: character.CharacterProgression | None = None
1546        if raw_progressions := payload.get("progressions"):
1547            progressions_ = self.deserialize_character_progressions(

1549            )

1552        if raw_render_data := payload.get("renderData"):
1553            render_data = self.deserialize_character_render_data(

1555            )

1558            collections.Mapping[int, records.CharacterRecord]

1560        if raw_char_records := payload.get("records"):
1561            character_records = self.deserialize_characters_records(
1562                raw_char_records["data"]
1563            )
1564
1565        item_components: components.ItemsComponent | None = None
1566        if raw_item_components := payload.get("itemComponents"):
1567            item_components = self.deserialize_items_component(raw_item_components)
1568
1569        nodes: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, records.Node]] = None
1570        if raw_nodes := payload.get("presentationNodes"):
1571            nodes = {
1572                int(node_hash): self._deserialize_node(node)
1573                for node_hash, node in raw_nodes["data"]["nodes"].items()
1574            }
1575

1577        if raw_collectibles := payload.get("collectibles"):
1578            collectibles = self._deserialize_collectible(raw_collectibles["data"])
1579

1581        if raw_currencies := payload.get("currencyLookups"):

1593            profile_records=None,
1594            item_components=item_components,
1595            currency_lookups=currency_lookups,

1597            nodes=nodes,
1598            loadouts=loadouts,
1599        )

class Framework(aiobungie.api.framework.Framework): 
  68class Framework(api.Framework):
  69    """The base deserialization framework implementation.
  70
  71    This framework is used to deserialize JSON responses from the REST client and turning them into a `aiobungie.crates` Python classes.
  72
  73    Example
  74    --------
  75    ```py
  76    import aiobungie
  77
  78    from aiobungie import traits
  79    from aiobungie import framework
  80    from aiobungie import crates
  81
  82    class MyClient(traits.Deserialize):
  83        rest = aiobungie.RESTClient("token")
  84        my_name = "Fate"
  85        my_code = 4275
  86
  87        @property # required method.
  88        def framework(self) -> framework.Empty:
  89            return framework.Empty()
  90
  91        async def my_memberships(self) -> tuple[crates.DestinyMembership, ...]:
  92            # Note, Do not call methods within objects, Since this is an empty
  93            # factory, The client reference that makes these calls will be `None`.
  94            response = await self.rest.fetch_membership(self.my_name, self.my_code)
  95            return self.factory.deserialize_destiny_memberships(response)
  96
  97    async def main() -> None:
  98        client = MyClient()
  99        async with client.rest:
 100            print(await client.my_memberships())
 101
 102    asyncio.run(main())
 103    ```
 104    """
 105
 106    __slots__ = ("_app",)

 334    def deserialize_clan(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> clans.Clan:
 335        current_user_map: collections.Mapping[str, clans.ClanMember] | None = None
 336        if raw_current_user := payload.get("currentUserMemberMap"):
 337            # This will get populated if only it was a GroupsV2.GroupResponse.
 338            # GroupsV2.GetGroupsForMemberResponse doesn't have this field.
 339            current_user_map = {
 340                membership_type: self.deserialize_clan_member(membership)
 341                for membership_type, membership in raw_current_user.items()
 342            }
 343
 344        return self._deserialize_group_details(
 345            data=payload["detail"],
 346            clan_founder=self.deserialize_clan_member(payload["founder"]),
 347            current_user_memberships=current_user_map,
 348        )

 439    def _set_character_attrs(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> character.Character:
 440        if raw_emblem_color := payload.get("emblemColor"):
 441            emblem_color: tuple[int, int, int, int] = (
 442                int(raw_emblem_color["red"]),
 443                int(raw_emblem_color["green"]),
 444                int(raw_emblem_color["blue"]),
 445                int(raw_emblem_color["alpha"]),
 446            )
 447        else:
 448            emblem_color = (0, 0, 0, 0)
 449
 450        return character.Character(
 451            id=int(payload["characterId"]),
 452            gender=enums.Gender(payload["genderType"]),
 453            race=enums.Race(payload["raceType"]),
 454            class_type=enums.Class(payload["classType"]),
 455            emblem=builders.Image(path=payload["emblemBackgroundPath"])
 456            if "emblemBackgroundPath" in payload
 457            else None,
 458            emblem_icon=builders.Image(path=payload["emblemPath"])
 459            if "emblemPath" in payload
 460            else None,
 461            emblem_hash=int(payload["emblemHash"]) if "emblemHash" in payload else None,
 462            last_played=time.clean_date(payload["dateLastPlayed"]),
 463            total_played_time=int(payload["minutesPlayedTotal"]),
 464            member_id=int(payload["membershipId"]),
 465            member_type=enums.MembershipType(payload["membershipType"]),
 466            level=payload["baseCharacterLevel"],
 467            title_hash=payload.get("titleRecordHash", None),
 468            light=payload["light"],
 469            stats={enums.Stat(int(k)): v for k, v in payload["stats"].items()},
 470            emblem_color=emblem_color,
 471            minutes_played_this_session=int(payload["minutesPlayedThisSession"])
 472            if "minutesPlayedThisSession" in payload
 473            else 0,
 474            percent_to_next_level=float(payload["percentToNextLevel"]),
 475        )

 535    def deserialize_records(
 536        self,
 537        payload: typedefs.JSONObject,
 538        scores: records.RecordScores | None = None,
 539        **nodes: int,
 540    ) -> records.Record:
 541        objectives: collections.Sequence[records.Objective] | None = None
 542        interval_objectives: collections.Sequence[records.Objective] | None = None
 543        record_state: records.RecordState | int
 544
 545        record_state = records.RecordState(payload["state"])
 546
 547        if raw_objs := payload.get("objectives"):
 548            objectives = tuple(self.deserialize_objectives(obj) for obj in raw_objs)
 549
 550        if raw_interval_objs := payload.get("intervalObjectives"):
 551            interval_objectives = tuple(
 552                self.deserialize_objectives(obj) for obj in raw_interval_objs
 553            )
 554
 555        return records.Record(
 556            scores=scores,
 557            categories_node_hash=nodes.get("categories_hash"),
 558            seals_node_hash=nodes.get("seals_hash"),
 559            state=record_state,
 560            objectives=objectives,
 561            interval_objectives=interval_objectives,
 562            redeemed_count=payload.get("intervalsRedeemedCount", 0),
 563            completion_times=payload.get("completedCount", None),
 564            reward_visibility=payload.get("rewardVisibility"),
 565        )

 832    def deserialize_milestone(
 833        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 834    ) -> milestones.Milestone:
 835        start_date: datetime.datetime | None = None
 836        if raw_start_date := payload.get("startDate"):
 837            start_date = time.clean_date(raw_start_date)
 838
 839        end_date: datetime.datetime | None = None
 840        if raw_end_date := payload.get("endDate"):
 841            end_date = time.clean_date(raw_end_date)
 842
 843        rewards: collections.Collection[milestones.MilestoneReward] | None = None
 844        if raw_rewards := payload.get("rewards"):
 845            rewards = tuple(
 846                self._deserialize_milestone_rewards(reward) for reward in raw_rewards
 847            )
 848
 849        activities: collections.Sequence[milestones.MilestoneActivity] | None = None
 850        if raw_activities := payload.get("activities"):
 851            activities = tuple(
 852                self._deserialize_milestone_activity(active)
 853                for active in raw_activities
 854            )
 855
 856        quests: collections.Sequence[milestones.MilestoneQuest] | None = None
 857        if raw_quests := payload.get("availableQuests"):
 858            quests = tuple(
 859                self._deserialize_milestone_available_quest(quest)
 860                for quest in raw_quests
 861            )
 862
 863        vendors: collections.Sequence[milestones.MilestoneVendor] | None = None
 864        if raw_vendors := payload.get("vendors"):
 865            vendors = tuple(
 866                milestones.MilestoneVendor(
 867                    vendor_hash=vendor["vendorHash"],
 868                    preview_itemhash=vendor.get("previewItemHash"),
 869                )
 870                for vendor in raw_vendors
 871            )
 872
 873        return milestones.Milestone(
 874            hash=payload["milestoneHash"],
 875            start_date=start_date,
 876            end_date=end_date,
 877            order=payload["order"],
 878            rewards=rewards,
 879            available_quests=quests,
 880            activities=activities,
 881            vendors=vendors,
 882        )

1114    def deserialize_components(  # noqa: C901 Too complex.
1115        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
1116    ) -> components.Component:
1117        # Due to how complex this method is, We'll stick to
1118        # typing.Optional here.
1119
1120        profile_: profile.Profile | None = None
1121        if raw_profile := payload.get("profile"):
1122            profile_ = self.deserialize_profile(raw_profile["data"])
1123
1124        profile_progression: profile.ProfileProgression | None = None
1125        if raw_profile_progression := payload.get("profileProgression"):
1126            profile_progression = self.deserialize_profile_progression(
1127                raw_profile_progression
1128            )
1129
1130        profile_currencies: typing.Optional[
1131            collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]
1132        ] = None
1133        if raw_profile_currencies := payload.get("profileCurrencies"):
1134            if "data" in raw_profile_currencies:
1135                profile_currencies = self.deserialize_profile_items(
1136                    raw_profile_currencies["data"]
1137                )
1138
1139        profile_inventories: typing.Optional[
1140            collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]
1141        ] = None
1142        if raw_profile_inventories := payload.get("profileInventory"):
1143            if "data" in raw_profile_inventories:
1144                profile_inventories = self.deserialize_profile_items(
1145                    raw_profile_inventories["data"]
1146                )
1147
1148        profile_records: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, records.Record]] = (
1149            None
1150        )
1151
1152        if raw_profile_records_ := payload.get("profileRecords"):
1153            profile_records = self.deserialize_profile_records(raw_profile_records_)
1154
1155        characters: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, character.Character]] = (
1156            None
1157        )
1158        if raw_characters := payload.get("characters"):
1159            characters = self.deserialize_characters(raw_characters)
1160
1161        character_records: typing.Optional[
1162            collections.Mapping[int, records.CharacterRecord]
1163        ] = None
1164
1165        if raw_character_records := payload.get("characterRecords"):
1166            # Had to do it in two steps..
1167            to_update = {}
1168            for _, data in raw_character_records["data"].items():
1169                for record_id, record in data.items():
1170                    to_update[record_id] = record
1171
1172            character_records = {
1173                int(rec_id): self.deserialize_character_records(
1174                    rec, record_hashes=to_update.get("featuredRecordHashes", ())
1175                )
1176                for rec_id, rec in to_update["records"].items()
1177            }
1178
1179        character_equipments: typing.Optional[
1180            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]]
1181        ] = None
1182        if raw_character_equips := payload.get("characterEquipment"):
1183            character_equipments = self.deserialize_character_equipments(
1184                raw_character_equips
1185            )
1186
1187        character_inventories: typing.Optional[
1188            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]]
1189        ] = None
1190        if raw_character_inventories := payload.get("characterInventories"):
1191            if "data" in raw_character_inventories:
1192                character_inventories = self.deserialize_character_equipments(
1193                    raw_character_inventories
1194                )
1195
1196        character_activities: typing.Optional[
1197            collections.Mapping[int, activity.CharacterActivity]
1198        ] = None
1199        if raw_char_acts := payload.get("characterActivities"):
1200            character_activities = self.deserialize_character_activities(raw_char_acts)
1201
1202        character_render_data: typing.Optional[
1203            collections.Mapping[int, character.RenderedData]
1204        ] = None
1205        if raw_character_render_data := payload.get("characterRenderData"):

1208            )

1210        character_progressions: typing.Optional[
1211            collections.Mapping[int, character.CharacterProgression]
1212        ] = None
1213
1214        if raw_character_progressions := payload.get("characterProgressions"):
1215            character_progressions = self.deserialize_character_progressions_mapping(
1216                raw_character_progressions
1217            )
1218
1219        profile_string_vars: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, int]] = None
1220        if raw_profile_string_vars := payload.get("profileStringVariables"):
1221            profile_string_vars = raw_profile_string_vars["data"]["integerValuesByHash"]
1222
1223        character_string_vars: typing.Optional[
1224            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Mapping[int, int]]
1225        ] = None
1226        if raw_character_string_vars := payload.get("characterStringVariables"):
1227            character_string_vars = {
1228                int(char_id): data["integerValuesByHash"]
1229                for char_id, data in raw_character_string_vars["data"].items()
1230            }
1231
1232        metrics: typing.Optional[
1233            collections.Sequence[
1234                collections.Mapping[int, tuple[bool, records.Objective | None]]

1236        ] = None

1238

1241            metrics = tuple(
1242                {
1243                    int(metrics_hash): (
1244                        data["invisible"],
1245                        self.deserialize_objectives(data["objectiveProgress"])
1246                        if "objectiveProgress" in data
1247                        else None,
1248                    )
1249                }
1250                for metrics_hash, data in raw_metrics["data"]["metrics"].items()
1251            )

1253        if raw_transitory := payload.get("profileTransitoryData"):
1254            if "data" in raw_transitory:
1255                transitory = self.deserialize_fireteam_party(raw_transitory["data"])
1256
1257        item_components: components.ItemsComponent | None = None
1258        if raw_item_components := payload.get("itemComponents"):
1259            item_components = self.deserialize_items_component(raw_item_components)

1270
1271        character_plugsets: typing.Optional[
1272            collections.Mapping[

1276        if raw_char_plugsets := payload.get("characterPlugSets"):
1277            character_plugsets = {
1278                int(char_id): {
1279                    int(index): [
1280                        self.deserialize_plug_item_state(state) for state in data
1281                    ]
1282                    for index, data in inner["plugs"].items()
1283                }
1284                for char_id, inner in raw_char_plugsets["data"].items()
1285            }
1286
1287        character_collectibles: typing.Optional[
1288            collections.Mapping[int, items.Collectible]
1289        ] = None
1290        if raw_character_collectibles := payload.get("characterCollectibles"):
1291            character_collectibles = {
1292                int(char_id): self._deserialize_collectible(data)
1293                for char_id, data in raw_character_collectibles["data"].items()
1294            }
1295
1296        profile_collectibles: items.Collectible | None = None
1297        if raw_profile_collectibles := payload.get("profileCollectibles"):
1298            profile_collectibles = self._deserialize_collectible(
1299                raw_profile_collectibles["data"]
1300            )
1301
1302        profile_nodes: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, records.Node]] = None
1303        if raw_profile_nodes := payload.get("profilePresentationNodes"):
1304            profile_nodes = {
1305                int(node_hash): self._deserialize_node(node)
1306                for node_hash, node in raw_profile_nodes["data"]["nodes"].items()
1307            }
1308
1309        character_nodes: typing.Optional[
1310            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Mapping[int, records.Node]]
1311        ] = None
1312        if raw_character_nodes := payload.get("characterPresentationNodes"):
1313            character_nodes = {
1314                int(char_id): {
1315                    int(node_hash): self._deserialize_node(node)
1316                    for node_hash, node in each_character["nodes"].items()
1317                }
1318                for char_id, each_character in raw_character_nodes["data"].items()
1319            }
1320
1321        platform_silver: typing.Optional[
1322            collections.Mapping[str, profile.ProfileItemImpl]
1323        ] = None
1324        if raw_platform_silver := payload.get("platformSilver"):
1325            if "data" in raw_platform_silver:
1326                platform_silver = {
1327                    platform_name: self.deserialize_profile_item(item)
1328                    for platform_name, item in raw_platform_silver["data"][
1329                        "platformSilver"
1330                    ].items()
1331                }
1332
1333        character_currency_lookups: typing.Optional[
1334            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[items.Currency]]
1335        ] = None
1336        if raw_char_lookups := payload.get("characterCurrencyLookups"):
1337            if "data" in raw_char_lookups:
1338                character_currency_lookups = {
1339                    int(char_id): self._deserialize_currencies(currency)
1340                    for char_id, currency in raw_char_lookups["data"].items()
1341                }
1342
1343        character_craftables: typing.Optional[
1344            collections.Mapping[int, components.CraftablesComponent]
1345        ] = None
1346        if raw_character_craftables := payload.get("characterCraftables"):
1347            if "data" in raw_character_craftables:
1348                character_craftables = {
1349                    int(char_id): self.deserialize_craftables_component(craftable)
1350                    for char_id, craftable in raw_character_craftables["data"].items()
1351                }
1352
1353        character_loadouts: (
1354            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[character.Loadout]] | None

1406    def deserialize_items_component(
1407        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
1408    ) -> components.ItemsComponent:
1409        # Due to how complex this method is, We'll stick to typing.Optional.
1410        instances: typing.Optional[
1411            collections.Sequence[collections.Mapping[int, items.ItemInstance]]
1412        ] = None
1413        if raw_instances := payload.get("instances"):
1414            instances = tuple(
1415                {int(ins_id): self.deserialize_instanced_item(item)}
1416                for ins_id, item in raw_instances["data"].items()
1417            )
1418
1419        render_data: typing.Optional[
1420            collections.Mapping[int, tuple[bool, dict[int, int]]]
1421        ] = None
1422        if raw_render_data := payload.get("renderData"):
1423            render_data = {
1424                int(ins_id): (data["useCustomDyes"], data["artRegions"])
1425                for ins_id, data in raw_render_data["data"].items()
1426            }
1427
1428        stats: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, items.ItemStatsView]] = None
1429        if raw_stats := payload.get("stats"):
1430            stats = {}
1431            for ins_id, stat in raw_stats["data"].items():
1432                for _, items_ in stat.items():
1433                    stats[int(ins_id)] = self.deserialize_item_stats_view(items_)
1434
1435        sockets: typing.Optional[
1436            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[items.ItemSocket]]
1437        ] = None
1438        if raw_sockets := payload.get("sockets"):
1439            sockets = {
1440                int(ins_id): tuple(
1441                    self.deserialize_item_socket(socket) for socket in item["sockets"]
1442                )
1443                for ins_id, item in raw_sockets["data"].items()
1444            }
1445
1446        objectives: typing.Optional[
1447            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[records.Objective]]
1448        ] = None
1449        if raw_objectives := payload.get("objectives"):
1450            objectives = {
1451                int(ins_id): tuple(
1452                    self.deserialize_objectives(objective)
1453                    for objective in data["objectives"]
1454                )
1455                for ins_id, data in raw_objectives["data"].items()
1456            }
1457
1458        perks: typing.Optional[
1459            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Collection[items.ItemPerk]]
1460        ] = None
1461        if raw_perks := payload.get("perks"):
1462            perks = {
1463                int(ins_id): tuple(
1464                    self.deserialize_item_perk(perk) for perk in item["perks"]
1465                )
1466                for ins_id, item in raw_perks["data"].items()
1467            }
1468
1469        plug_states: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[items.PlugItemState]] = None
1470        if raw_plug_states := payload.get("plugStates"):
1471            plug_states = tuple(
1472                self.deserialize_plug_item_state(plug)
1473                for _, plug in raw_plug_states["data"].items()
1474            )
1475
1476        reusable_plugs: typing.Optional[
1477            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[items.PlugItemState]]
1478        ] = None
1479        if raw_re_plugs := payload.get("reusablePlugs"):
1480            reusable_plugs = {
1481                int(ins_id): tuple(
1482                    self.deserialize_plug_item_state(state) for state in inner
1483                )
1484                for ins_id, plug in raw_re_plugs["data"].items()
1485                for inner in tuple(plug["plugs"].values())
1486            }
1487
1488        plug_objectives: typing.Optional[
1489            collections.Mapping[
1490                int, collections.Mapping[int, collections.Collection[records.Objective]]
1491            ]
1492        ] = None
1493        if raw_plug_objectives := payload.get("plugObjectives"):
1494            plug_objectives = {
1495                int(ins_id): {
1496                    int(obj_hash): tuple(
1497                        self.deserialize_objectives(obj) for obj in objs
1498                    )
1499                    for obj_hash, objs in inner["objectivesPerPlug"].items()
1500                }
1501                for ins_id, inner in raw_plug_objectives["data"].items()
1502            }
1503
1504        return components.ItemsComponent(
1505            sockets=sockets,
1506            stats=stats,
1507            render_data=render_data,
1508            instances=instances,
1509            objectives=objectives,
1510            perks=perks,
1511            plug_states=plug_states,
1512            reusable_plugs=reusable_plugs,
1513            plug_objectives=plug_objectives,
1514        )

1516    def deserialize_character_component(
1517        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
1518    ) -> components.CharacterComponent:
1519        character_: character.Character | None = None
1520        if raw_singular_character := payload.get("character"):
1521            character_ = self.deserialize_character(raw_singular_character["data"])
1522
1523        inventory: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]] = None
1524        loadouts: collections.Sequence[character.Loadout] | None = None
1525        if raw_inventory := payload.get("inventory"):
1526            if "data" in raw_inventory:
1527                inventory = self.deserialize_profile_items(raw_inventory["data"])
1528
1529            # The inventory component also returns the loadouts component
1530            if raw_loadouts := payload.get("loadouts"):
1531                if "data" in raw_loadouts:
1532                    loadouts = tuple(
1533                        self.deserialize_character_loadout(loadout)
1534                        # very interesting nesting bungie...
1535                        for loadout in raw_loadouts["data"]["loadouts"]
1536                    )
1537
1538        activities: activity.CharacterActivity | None = None
1539        if raw_activities := payload.get("activities"):
1540            activities = self.deserialize_character_activity(raw_activities["data"])
1541
1542        equipment: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]] = None
1543        if raw_equipments := payload.get("equipment"):
1544            equipment = self.deserialize_profile_items(raw_equipments["data"])
1545
1546        progressions_: character.CharacterProgression | None = None
1547        if raw_progressions := payload.get("progressions"):
1548            progressions_ = self.deserialize_character_progressions(
1549                raw_progressions["data"]
1550            )
1551
1552        render_data: character.RenderedData | None = None
1553        if raw_render_data := payload.get("renderData"):
1554            render_data = self.deserialize_character_render_data(
1555                raw_render_data["data"]
1556            )
1557
1558        character_records: typing.Optional[
1559            collections.Mapping[int, records.CharacterRecord]
1560        ] = None
1561        if raw_char_records := payload.get("records"):
1562            character_records = self.deserialize_characters_records(
1563                raw_char_records["data"]
1564            )
1565
1566        item_components: components.ItemsComponent | None = None
1567        if raw_item_components := payload.get("itemComponents"):
1568            item_components = self.deserialize_items_component(raw_item_components)
1569
1570        nodes: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, records.Node]] = None
1571        if raw_nodes := payload.get("presentationNodes"):
1572            nodes = {
1573                int(node_hash): self._deserialize_node(node)
1574                for node_hash, node in raw_nodes["data"]["nodes"].items()
1575            }
1576
1577        collectibles: items.Collectible | None = None
1578        if raw_collectibles := payload.get("collectibles"):
1579            collectibles = self._deserialize_collectible(raw_collectibles["data"])
1580
1581        currency_lookups: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[items.Currency]] = None
1582        if raw_currencies := payload.get("currencyLookups"):
1583            if "data" in raw_currencies:
1584                currency_lookups = self._deserialize_currencies(raw_currencies)
1585
1586        return components.CharacterComponent(
1587            activities=activities,
1588            equipment=equipment,
1589            inventory=inventory,
1590            progressions=progressions_,
1591            render_data=render_data,
1592            character=character_,
1593            character_records=character_records,
1594            profile_records=None,
1595            item_components=item_components,
1596            currency_lookups=currency_lookups,
1597            collectibles=collectibles,
1598            nodes=nodes,
1599            loadouts=loadouts,
1600        )

1602    def _set_entity_attrs(
1603        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject, *, key: str = "displayProperties"
1604    ) -> entity.Entity:
1605        properties = payload[key]
1606        name = typedefs.unknown(properties["name"])

The base deserialization framework implementation.

This framework is used to deserialize JSON responses from the REST client and turning them into a aiobungie.crates Python classes.

Example
import aiobungie

from aiobungie import traits
from aiobungie import framework
from aiobungie import crates

class MyClient(traits.Deserialize):
    rest = aiobungie.RESTClient("token")
    my_name = "Fate"
    my_code = 4275

    @property # required method.
    def framework(self) -> framework.Empty:
        return framework.Empty()

    async def my_memberships(self) -> tuple[crates.DestinyMembership, ...]:
        # Note, Do not call methods within objects, Since this is an empty
        # factory, The client reference that makes these calls will be `None`.
        response = await self.rest.fetch_membership(self.my_name, self.my_code)
        return self.factory.deserialize_destiny_memberships(response)

async def main() -> None:
    client = MyClient()
    async with client.rest:
        print(await client.my_memberships())

asyncio.run(main())
